The paper proposes a framework for fleet management using reinforcement learning, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The framework involves coordination among a large number of agents, which suggests the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The problem setting involves complex dynamics and stochastic demand-supply variations, which suggests the category of robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY).
